<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by a_necro52 on 06-07-2001 08:36 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Oh yea, BTW, I did wrote an item editor just for grins (actually, I had always wanted to have a "Staff of Twinking", now I have one  :), it's not done really, when it is done (and if I get an account here) I'll post it. But I analyzed the skill part of the item struct and came up with roughly this (at least, this is what my editor uses).....


struct sNameValue
{
	const char* name;
	WORD value;
};

sNameValue Skills[] = 
{
	{"1H Slashing",		0x00},
	{"2H Slashing",		0x01},
	{"Piercing",		0x02},
	{"1H Blunt",		0x03},
	{"2H Blunt",		0x04},
	{"Archery",			0x05},
	{"Throwing? (magical)",		0x07},
	{"Bashing (Shields)",	0x08},
	{"Armor",			0x0a},
	{"Pick Locks",		0x0c},
	{"Food",			0x0e},
	{"Drink",			0x0f},
	{"Light Object",	0x10},
	{"Trade Skill Component",	0x11},
	{"Bind Wound",		0x12},
	{"Throwing",		0x13},
	{"Scribable Spell",	0x14},
	{"Potion",			0x15},
	{"Flutes and Horns",	0x17},
	{"Stringed",		0x18},
	{"Brass",			0x19},
	{"Percussion",		0x1a},
	{"Arrows",			0x1b},
	{"Jewelry",			0x1d},
	{"Jewled Skull",	0x1e},
	{"Illegible quest items",	0x20},
	{"Key",				0x21},
	{"2H Piercing",		0x23},
	{"Fishing Pole",	0x24},
	{"Fishing Bait",	0x25},
	{"Alcoholic Beverage",	0x26},
	{"Key for a quest.",0x27},
	{"Compass",			0x28},
	{"Poison Sac",		0x2a},
	{"Trade skill book",0x3d},
	{"Hand-Made Backpack",	0x62},
	{"Tailored Large Bag",	0xd3}
};

sNameValue ItemTypes[] =
{
	{"Normal", 0},
	{"Container", 1},
	{"Book", 2}
};

sNameValue Sizes[] = 
{
	{"Tiny", 0},
	{"Small", 1},
	{"Medium", 2},
	{"Large", 3},
	{"Giant", 4}
};

So it's not only used to match up combat skills, but also to identify an item as an alchoholic beverage, food, a trade skill component (i.e., a silk swatch or a small piece of ore are things that fit in this one), etc. Then there were a few odd ones as well...</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
